hashtag buildthewall from the pacific ocean to the gulf of mexico - hashtag deport all illegals and their families - hashtag nodaca hashtag noamnesty - hashtag proudamerica hashtag americafirst hashtag votered
I see a lot of anger and fear behind those hashtags. But what about the families who have been here for years, working hard, paying taxes, and contributing to the community? Don't they deserve a chance to stay and build a better life for themselves and their children?
